### Algorithm ###

Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Initialize two integer variables, a with the value 208 and b with the value 600.
Step 3: Calculate and print the boolean results (True or False) of various algebraic identities (like squares and cubes) to verify equation assignment operators.
Step 4: Calculate and print the boolean results of different bitwise operations (AND &, OR |, XOR ^) to demonstrate their mathematical relationships.
Step 5: Verify and print the boolean results of addition operations using their bitwise equivalents.
Step 6: Verify and print the boolean results of subtraction operations using their bitwise equivalents.
Step 7: Stop the program.



